A utility library for Atmel AVR microcontrollers.

The project build assumes a directory structure like this:

src
|
+-apps
|
+-libs
| |
| +-avrutil
|
+-3rd

*** BUILDING ON WINDOWS ***

You will need WinAVR (I used WinAVR-20090313) from here:

  http://winavr.sourceforge.net

Then just do this:

  make -f Makefile.avr                 (for the default at90usb162)
  make -f Makefile.avr MCU=atmega162   (for the atmega162)


*** BUILDING ON LINUX ***

You will need gcc-avr and avr-libc, e.g

  sudo apt-get install gcc-avr
  sudo apt-get install avr-libc

  make -f Makefile.avr                 (for the default at90usb162)
  make -f Makefile.avr MCU=atmega162   (for the atmega162)
